    "thought": "The case description can be divided into the following scenes:",
    "scripts": [
        "Scene 1: The setting is a cold winter night at a city library after closing hours. The librarian, Old Li, discovers a deceased male body while tidying up the bookshelves.",
        "Scene 2: The deceased individual is identified as a renowned local writer, and preliminary assessment suggests the cause of death to be cardiac arrest.",
        "Scene 3: The crime scene exhibits no obvious signs of violence, yet the deceased is found clutching an ancient book with red stains on its pages, seemingly blood.",
        "Scene 4: The library's surveillance footage reveals that only the deceased entered the area where the body was found on that particular night.",
        "Scene 5: The player is presented with the task of deducing the circumstances surrounding the death, having five questions to uncover further details."
    ]
